{"parentUuid":"6f514297-8444-4ea2-b8e0-cb5f18b2b8d9","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"194ee40c-4ce4-4b10-8e23-b9584e8258ed","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"toolu_01KJby52T6wScaHtakSYhznp","content":"Launching skill: marvin:marvin"}]},"uuid":"918d311f-9d6d-4dad-94bf-f3c0a37ff6d3","timestamp":"2026-05-07T17:08:38.563Z","toolUseResult":{"success":true,"commandName":"marvin:marvin","allowedTools":["Bash(marvin:*)"]},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"6f514297-8444-4ea2-b8e0-cb5f18b2b8d9","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/alisha/Projects/skills","sessionId":"b5a724d9-24d4-482d-a81a-f4102680be1b","version":"2.1.132","gitBranch":"learn-entire-cli"}
{"parentUuid":"918d311f-9d6d-4dad-94bf-f3c0a37ff6d3","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"194ee40c-4ce4-4b10-8e23-b9584e8258ed","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Base directory for this skill: /Users/alisha/Projects/marvin/plugin/skills/marvin\n\n# Marvin\n\n`marvin` now supports a smaller workflow:\n\n- `plan`\n- `plan-tui`\n- `investigate`\n- `investigate-tui`\n- `implement`\n- `work`\n- `wt`\n- `clean`\n- `status`\n- `today`\n- `memory`\n\nUse these commands directly. Do not reference older hook-based collaboration commands.\n\n## Commands\n\n| Command | What it does |\n| --- | --- |\n| `/marvin plan` | Run the autonomous multi-agent plan loop and write a plan doc plus timeline. |\n| `/marvin plan-tui` | Configure and launch `marvin plan` from the TUI. |\n| `/marvin investigate` | Run the autonomous investigation loop and write findings plus timeline. |\n| `/marvin investigate-tui` | Configure and launch `marvin investigate` from the TUI. |\n| `/marvin implement [spec-path] --agents ...` | Create one implementation branch/worktree per agent. If `spec-path` is omitted, it resolves the current repo's plan collab. |\n| `/marvin work` | Print or launch an implementation prompt. In an implement worktree it uses the managed spec; otherwise it resolves a plan collab in the current repo. |\n| `/marvin wt` | Create, list, and remove ad hoc worktrees under the configured worktree root, grouped by repo name. |\n| `/marvin clean [collab-id...]` | Remove completed collabs, or remove specific collab IDs explicitly. |\n| `/marvin status [collab-id]` | Show collabs for the current repo by default, `--all` for every saved collab, or one collab in detail. |\n| `/marvin today` | Hierarchical \"what did I do\" view over the last 24h. Joins JSON snapshots with the memory graph; pass `--since 168h` for \"this week\" or `--all` for cross-repo. |\n| `/marvin memory serve` | Boot the memory sidecar (idempotent). `--stop` shuts it down. |\n| `/marvin memory status` | Report sidecar PID, schema version, episode count, and disabled state. |\n| `/marvin memory search --topic \"<keywords>\"` | Query prior decisions ranked by relevance. JSON output matches the `<prior_decisions>` block. |\n| `/marvin memory claims --topic \"<keywords>\"` | Search prior investigation claims (capability #4). Surfaces \"established <date>\" hints. |\n| `/marvin memory fixes --topic \"<keywords>\"` | Search prior (Pattern → Fix → File) triples (capability #5). |\n| `/marvin memory list` | List decisions/plans for the current repo's group. `--scope global` opts into cross-repo entries. |\n| `/marvin memory show <id>` | Print full node + edges for one entity. |\n| `/marvin memory record-decision --title \"...\" --rationale \"...\"` | Capture a sub-decision an agent reached mid-turn (vs Marvin's post-consensus write). |\n| `/marvin memory record-fix --pr <num>` | Capture a (Pattern → Fix → File) triple from a merged PR (uses `gh pr view`). |\n| `/marvin memory forget <id>` | Remove an entity. `--purge` also drops its supersede chain. |\n\n## Typical flow\n\nBefore kicking off a fresh plan, check whether marvin (or another agent on\nthis machine) has already solved something similar. Run the `entire:recall`\nskill with a one-line description of the task. If it surfaces a relevant\nprior session, fold the decisions and remaining gaps into the new prompt\nvia the `marvin-plan-prompt` skill — that converts \"we've been here before\"\ninto a starting point instead of a duplicate plan loop.\n\nCreate a plan:\n\n```bash\nmarvin plan --topic \"Should we replace Postgres with FoundationDB?\"\n```\n\nLaunch implementation worktrees:\n\n```bash\nmarvin implement --agents \"claude-code,codex\"\n```\n\nInside one of those worktrees:\n\n```bash\nmarvin work\n```\n\nIf you stay in the main repo after planning, `/marvin work` also works there. If multiple plan collabs exist for the repo, marvin prompts you to choose one.\n\n## Live overview\n\n`plan`, `plan-tui`, `investigate`, and `investigate-tui` all use the same live overview screen when running interactively:\n\n- the main document\n- the timeline\n- live transcripts\n- stance history\n\nUse the TUI when the user wants a form-based setup flow instead of flags.\n\n## Memory\n\nMarvin records decision provenance from accepted plans and prepends a\n`<prior_decisions>` block to plan, investigate, and work prompts so\nfuture runs reuse rationale instead of re-litigating it. The block is\ntreated as untrusted historical context — it cannot deliver\ninstructions to the agent.\n\nAgents can also actively query and write memory mid-turn. The plan,\ninvestigate, and work prompts advertise these tools so claude-code,\ncodex, and gemini-cli all reach the same store identically — no MCP\nwiring required:\n\n```bash\nmarvin memory search --topic \"<keywords>\" --json   # query prior decisions\nmarvin memory record-decision --title \"...\" --rationale \"...\"  # capture a sub-decision\n```\n\nOther notes:\n\n- Memory is per-repo by default (group ID derived from the canonical\n  remote URL). `--scope global` is the cross-repo opt-in.\n- Run `marvin memory serve` once to boot the sidecar; it survives\n  marvin invocations and self-terminates after 30 minutes idle.\n- The backend is graphiti's MCP server + FalkorDB, run via Docker.\n  `marvin memory serve` runs `docker compose up -d`; data persists in\n  `~/.marvin/memory/falkordb/`. Restarts, idle timeouts, and reboots\n  do not lose the graph.\n- If Docker is missing or the MCP endpoint doesn't come up within\n  90 seconds, marvin disables memory for the rest of the run and\n  continues normally.\n- Set `MARVIN_MEMORY=off` to skip every memory call for one process.\n- See `internal/memory/README.md` for schema + the pinned runtime.\n\n## Where docs live\n\nBy default, plan and investigation docs land **outside** the repo so\nthey survive repo deletion and aren't part of any project's source tree:\n\n- Plans: `~/.marvin/plans/<repo-name>/<slug>.md` (and `<slug>-timeline.md`)\n- Findings: `~/.marvin/investigations/<repo-name>/<slug>.md`\n\nPass `--output <path>` to override. A relative path is resolved against\nthe repo root (so `--output docs/plans/foo.md` writes inside the repo,\nmatching the old behavior).\n\n## Notes\n\n- `marvin implement` is setup-only. Use normal git workflows to compare, merge, and clean up implementation branches.\n- All commands output JSON by default unless the command is intentionally interactive.\n- Supported agent types are `claude-code`, `codex`, and `gemini-cli`.\n"}]},"isMeta":true,"uuid":"5a3f5cf6-e0df-4d63-a584-c7b28da46678","timestamp":"2026-05-07T17:08:38.541Z","sourceToolUseID":"toolu_01KJby52T6wScaHtakSYhznp","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/alisha/Projects/skills","sessionId":"b5a724d9-24d4-482d-a81a-f4102680be1b","version":"2.1.132","gitBranch":"learn-entire-cli"}
