{"parentUuid":"44eeba04-f144-4e54-a2bc-7c2414edef5d","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_012Jp4thjPF38TxV1dnxkTVy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01CYJqb55CtiqTusxdMrxhy1","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/alisha/Projects/skills/README.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1458,"cache_read_input_tokens":63090,"output_tokens":236,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1458,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":236,"cache_read_input_tokens":63090,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1458,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1458},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CaoaS9YSSzF9uNaGnzTBZ","attributionSkill":"marvin:marvin","attributionPlugin":"marvin","type":"assistant","uuid":"165ac60a-7f3d-4d16-8005-e40870791d77","timestamp":"2026-05-07T17:08:56.571Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/alisha/Projects/skills","sessionId":"b5a724d9-24d4-482d-a81a-f4102680be1b","version":"2.1.132","gitBranch":"learn-entire-cli"}
{"parentUuid":"165ac60a-7f3d-4d16-8005-e40870791d77","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"194ee40c-4ce4-4b10-8e23-b9584e8258ed","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CYJqb55CtiqTusxdMrxhy1","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t![skills cover](assets/gh-repo-cover.png)\n2\t\n3\t# skills\n4\t\n5\tBring your Entire context to your agents with cross-agent skills.\n6\t\n7\t## Why This Exists\n8\t\n9\tThe [Entire CLI](https://github.com/entireio/cli) captures the context behind your\n10\tcode changes: prompts, transcripts,\n11\t[Checkpoints](https://docs.entire.io/cli/checkpoints), and the decisions that led\n12\tto each change, alongside your git history. This repository packages\n13\tagent-invokable workflows that teach coding agents how to use that context across\n14\tdevelopment environments.\n15\t\n16\tInstead of looking up Entire commands yourself, you can ask in plain language and\n17\tlet your agent search prior work, inspect provenance, hand off session state, or\n18\tturn repeated workflows into new skills.\n19\t\n20\t## Install\n21\t\n22\tInstall every skill with the [skills](https://skills.sh/) CLI:\n23\t\n24\t```bash\n25\tnpx skills add https://github.com/entireio/skills --all\n26\t```\n27\t\n28\tInstall one skill:\n29\t\n30\t```bash\n31\tnpx skills add https://github.com/entireio/skills --skill search\n32\t```\n33\t\n34\tSee [Agent-Specific Installation](#agent-specific-installation) for setup\n35\tinstructions by agent.\n36\t\n37\t## Quick Start\n38\t\n39\t> [!NOTE]\n40\t> These skills are most useful in codebases with real\n41\t> [Checkpoints](https://docs.entire.io/cli/checkpoints) and session history. The\n42\t> richer the history, the more context your agent has to work with; in a new or\n43\t> lightly captured repository, some workflows may have less to find or explain.\n44\t\n45\tAfter installing, ask your agent for the workflow you want:\n46\t\n47\t```text\n48\tsearch past work for rate limiting\n49\t```\n50\t\n51\t```text\n52\texplain src/auth.ts\n53\t```\n54\t\n55\t```text\n56\twhat happened here: src/auth.ts:42-57\n57\t```\n58\t\n59\t```text\n60\thand off this session\n61\t```\n62\t\n63\t```text\n64\tturn my release notes workflow into a skill\n65\t```\n66\t\n67\tFor a guided walkthrough, see the\n68\t[skills tutorial](https://docs.entire.io/skills/tutorial).\n69\t\n70\t## What skills help agents do\n71\t\n72\t| Goal | Example prompt |\n73\t| --- | --- |\n74\t| Find prior work before making changes | `search past work for the migration` |\n75\t| Understand the intent behind a function, file, or line | `explain parseConfig` |\n76\t| Investigate the latest change to a specific block | `what happened at src/auth.ts:42` |\n77\t| Pick up another agent's work | `hand off the codex session` |\n78\t| Convert repeated work into a reusable workflow | `make a skill from this session` |\n79\t\n80\t## Included skills\n81\t\n82\tThe current repository includes these skills. Each skill lives in\n83\t`skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md`.\n84\t\n85\t### `search`\n86\t\n87\tFinds prior work in your Entire history by topic, repo, branch, author, or time\n88\twindow, so your agent can bring past context into the current task before making\n89\tchanges.\n90\t\n91\thttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/52e50eae-ba53-4f31-ad2e-2a29a767a34f\n92\t\n93\t### `explain`\n94\t\n95\tLooks up the session behind a function, file, or line so your agent can explain\n96\tthe requirement, decision, or original problem that shaped it.\n97\t\n98\thttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/ab2e88f6-9bce-417b-ba71-6e93ecad370b\n99\t\n100\t### `what-happened`\n101\t\n102\tStarts from an exact file line, range, or pasted snippet and traces the latest\n103\tchange with `git blame` and Checkpoint context. Useful when reviewing a concrete\n104\tblock, debugging a regression, or asking why that block changed.\n105\t\n106\thttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/47db0daa-60bd-4000-b956-2d0e4d980b9b\n107\t\n108\t### `session-handoff`\n109\t\n110\tReads saved or active session context so another agent can pick up the task\n111\tstate, important discoveries, blockers, and next steps without making you\n112\treconstruct everything manually.\n113\t\n114\thttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0df3b5cd-fe37-4145-af48-138642ccc8bc\n115\t\n116\t## Requirements\n117\t\n118\tThese skills are designed for repositories where Entire has captured useful\n119\thistory. Some workflows need:\n120\t\n121\t- the [Entire CLI](https://github.com/entireio/cli) installed\n122\t- a git repository with Entire sessions, Checkpoints, or Checkpoint-backed commits\n123\t- [`entire login`](https://docs.entire.io/cli/commands#login) for workflows that\n124\t  search indexed history\n125\t- a GitHub `origin` and pushed, indexed Checkpoints for remote search results\n126\t\n127\tIndividual skills handle missing context differently and should explain what is\n128\tmissing before falling back or stopping.\n129\t\n130\t## Agent-Specific Installation\n131\t\n132\t<!-- prettier-ignore-start -->\n133\t\n134\t<details>\n135\t<summary>Claude Code</summary>\n136\t\n137\t```bash\n138\t/plugin marketplace add entireio/skills\n139\t/plugin install entire\n140\t```\n141\t\n142\t</details>\n143\t\n144\t<details>\n145\t<summary>Codex (OpenAI)</summary>\n146\t\n147\tClone into the cross-client discovery path:\n148\t\n149\t```bash\n150\tgit clone https://github.com/entireio/skills.git ~/.agents/skills/entire\n151\t```\n152\t\n153\tCodex auto-discovers skills from `~/.agents/skills/` and `.agents/skills/`.\n154\tUpdate with:\n155\t\n156\t```bash\n157\tcd ~/.agents/skills/entire && git pull\n158\t```\n159\t\n160\t</details>\n161\t\n162\t<details>\n163\t<summary>Cursor</summary>\n164\t\n165\tCopy skills into the cross-client discovery directory:\n166\t\n167\t```bash\n168\tgit clone https://github.com/entireio/skills.git ~/.cursor/skills/entire\n169\t```\n170\t\n171\tCursor auto-discovers skills from `.agents/skills/` and `.cursor/skills/`.\n172\t\n173\t</details>\n174\t\n175\t<details>\n176\t<summary>Copilot</summary>\n177\t\n178\t```bash\n179\t/plugin install https://github.com/entireio/skills\n180\t# or\n181\tgit clone https://github.com/entireio/skills.git ~/.copilot/skills/entire\n182\t```\n183\t\n184\tCopilot auto-discovers skills from `.copilot/skills/`.\n185\t\n186\t</details>\n187\t\n188\t<details>\n189\t<summary>Gemini CLI</summary>\n190\t\n191\t```bash\n192\tgemini extensions install https://github.com/entireio/skills\n193\t```\n194\t\n195\tUpdate with:\n196\t\n197\t```bash\n198\tgemini extensions update entire\n199\t```\n200\t\n201\t</details>\n202\t\n203\t<details>\n204\t<summary>OpenCode</summary>\n205\t\n206\tCopy skills into the cross-client discovery directory:\n207\t\n208\t```bash\n209\tgit clone https://github.com/entireio/skills.git ~/.agents/skills/entire\n210\t```\n211\t\n212\tOpenCode auto-discovers skills from `.agents/skills/`, `.opencode/skills/`, and\n213\t`.claude/skills/`.\n214\t\n215\t</details>\n216\t\n217\t<!-- prettier-ignore-end -->\n218\t\n219\t## Contributing\n220\t\n221\tSee [CONTRIBUTING.md](CONTRIBUTING.md) for local development, validation, and pull\n222\trequest guidance. Please also follow the\n223\t[Code of Conduct](https://github.com/entireio/.github/blob/main/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md).\n224\t\n225\t## Support\n226\t\n227\tFor bugs, feature requests, or questions, open a\n228\t[GitHub issue](https://github.com/entireio/skills/issues). You can also join the\n229\t[Entire Community Discord Server](https://discord.gg/jZJs3Tue4S).\n230\t\n231\t## License\n232\t\n233\tThis project is licensed under the terms in [LICENSE](LICENSE).\n234\t"}]},"uuid":"296cd0fc-999c-4e5d-ab92-0196cb0b9d92","timestamp":"2026-05-07T17:08:56.579Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/alisha/Projects/skills/README.md","content":"![skills cover](assets/gh-repo-cover.png)\n\n# skills\n\nBring your Entire context to your agents with cross-agent skills.\n\n## Why This Exists\n\nThe [Entire CLI](https://github.com/entireio/cli) captures the context behind your\ncode changes: prompts, transcripts,\n[Checkpoints](https://docs.entire.io/cli/checkpoints), and the decisions that led\nto each change, alongside your git history. This repository packages\nagent-invokable workflows that teach coding agents how to use that context across\ndevelopment environments.\n\nInstead of looking up Entire commands yourself, you can ask in plain language and\nlet your agent search prior work, inspect provenance, hand off session state, or\nturn repeated workflows into new skills.\n\n## Install\n\nInstall every skill with the [skills](https://skills.sh/) CLI:\n\n```bash\nnpx skills add https://github.com/entireio/skills --all\n```\n\nInstall one skill:\n\n```bash\nnpx skills add https://github.com/entireio/skills --skill search\n```\n\nSee [Agent-Specific Installation](#agent-specific-installation) for setup\ninstructions by agent.\n\n## Quick Start\n\n> [!NOTE]\n> These skills are most useful in codebases with real\n> [Checkpoints](https://docs.entire.io/cli/checkpoints) and session history. The\n> richer the history, the more context your agent has to work with; in a new or\n> lightly captured repository, some workflows may have less to find or explain.\n\nAfter installing, ask your agent for the workflow you want:\n\n```text\nsearch past work for rate limiting\n```\n\n```text\nexplain src/auth.ts\n```\n\n```text\nwhat happened here: src/auth.ts:42-57\n```\n\n```text\nhand off this session\n```\n\n```text\nturn my release notes workflow into a skill\n```\n\nFor a guided walkthrough, see the\n[skills tutorial](https://docs.entire.io/skills/tutorial).\n\n## What skills help agents do\n\n| Goal | Example prompt |\n| --- | --- |\n| Find prior work before making changes | `search past work for the migration` |\n| Understand the intent behind a function, file, or line | `explain parseConfig` |\n| Investigate the latest change to a specific block | `what happened at src/auth.ts:42` |\n| Pick up another agent's work | `hand off the codex session` |\n| Convert repeated work into a reusable workflow | `make a skill from this session` |\n\n## Included skills\n\nThe current repository includes these skills. Each skill lives in\n`skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md`.\n\n### `search`\n\nFinds prior work in your Entire history by topic, repo, branch, author, or time\nwindow, so your agent can bring past context into the current task before making\nchanges.\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/52e50eae-ba53-4f31-ad2e-2a29a767a34f\n\n### `explain`\n\nLooks up the session behind a function, file, or line so your agent can explain\nthe requirement, decision, or original problem that shaped it.\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/ab2e88f6-9bce-417b-ba71-6e93ecad370b\n\n### `what-happened`\n\nStarts from an exact file line, range, or pasted snippet and traces the latest\nchange with `git blame` and Checkpoint context. Useful when reviewing a concrete\nblock, debugging a regression, or asking why that block changed.\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/47db0daa-60bd-4000-b956-2d0e4d980b9b\n\n### `session-handoff`\n\nReads saved or active session context so another agent can pick up the task\nstate, important discoveries, blockers, and next steps without making you\nreconstruct everything manually.\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0df3b5cd-fe37-4145-af48-138642ccc8bc\n\n## Requirements\n\nThese skills are designed for repositories where Entire has captured useful\nhistory. Some workflows need:\n\n- the [Entire CLI](https://github.com/entireio/cli) installed\n- a git repository with Entire sessions, Checkpoints, or Checkpoint-backed commits\n- [`entire login`](https://docs.entire.io/cli/commands#login) for workflows that\n  search indexed history\n- a GitHub `origin` and pushed, indexed Checkpoints for remote search results\n\nIndividual skills handle missing context differently and should explain what is\nmissing before falling back or stopping.\n\n## Agent-Specific Installation\n\n<!-- prettier-ignore-start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>Claude Code</summary>\n\n```bash\n/plugin marketplace add entireio/skills\n/plugin install entire\n```\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>Codex (OpenAI)</summary>\n\nClone into the cross-client discovery path:\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/entireio/skills.git ~/.agents/skills/entire\n```\n\nCodex auto-discovers skills from `~/.agents/skills/` and `.agents/skills/`.\nUpdate with:\n\n```bash\ncd ~/.agents/skills/entire && git pull\n```\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>Cursor</summary>\n\nCopy skills into the cross-client discovery directory:\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/entireio/skills.git ~/.cursor/skills/entire\n```\n\nCursor auto-discovers skills from `.agents/skills/` and `.cursor/skills/`.\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>Copilot</summary>\n\n```bash\n/plugin install https://github.com/entireio/skills\n# or\ngit clone https://github.com/entireio/skills.git ~/.copilot/skills/entire\n```\n\nCopilot auto-discovers skills from `.copilot/skills/`.\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>Gemini CLI</summary>\n\n```bash\ngemini extensions install https://github.com/entireio/skills\n```\n\nUpdate with:\n\n```bash\ngemini extensions update entire\n```\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>OpenCode</summary>\n\nCopy skills into the cross-client discovery directory:\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/entireio/skills.git ~/.agents/skills/entire\n```\n\nOpenCode auto-discovers skills from `.agents/skills/`, `.opencode/skills/`, and\n`.claude/skills/`.\n\n</details>\n\n<!-- prettier-ignore-end -->\n\n## Contributing\n\nSee [CONTRIBUTING.md](CONTRIBUTING.md) for local development, validation, and pull\nrequest guidance. Please also follow the\n[Code of Conduct](https://github.com/entireio/.github/blob/main/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md).\n\n## Support\n\nFor bugs, feature requests, or questions, open a\n[GitHub issue](https://github.com/entireio/skills/issues). You can also join the\n[Entire Community Discord Server](https://discord.gg/jZJs3Tue4S).\n\n## License\n\nThis project is licensed under the terms in [LICENSE](LICENSE).\n","numLines":234,"startLine":1,"totalLines":234}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"165ac60a-7f3d-4d16-8005-e40870791d77","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/alisha/Projects/skills","sessionId":"b5a724d9-24d4-482d-a81a-f4102680be1b","version":"2.1.132","gitBranch":"learn-entire-cli"}
